## Enable PowerTools (required for many dependencies)
dnf config-manager --set-enabled powertools

### Install EPEL
dnf install -y epel-release

###Enable specific Ruby and Node.js modules required for OOD 4.0+
### (OOD 4.x typically uses Ruby 3.x and Node 20)
dnf module enable -y ruby:3.1 nodejs:22
dnf install https://yum.osc.edu/ondemand/4.1/ondemand-release-web-4.1-1.el8.noarch.rpm
dnf install ondemand
dnf install -y mod_auth_openidc


## After generating the config file /etc/ood/config/ood_portal.yml ##

1. **Generate and Apply the Apache Config:**
## Open OnDemand uses a script to convert that YAML file into a standard Apache `.conf` file.

# Generate the Apache config
/opt/ood/ood-portal-generator/bin/generate -c /etc/ood/config/ood_portal.yml -o /etc/httpd/conf.d/ood-portal.conf

# Test the Apache syntax to ensure it doesn't clash with your other services
sudo apachectl configtest

### 3. Verification

If the `configtest` returns "Syntax OK", restart Apache:
sudo systemctl restart httpd
